# closeclaw Development Guidelines

Auto-generated from all feature plans. Last updated: 2026-04-05

## Constitution (SUPREME AUTHORITY)

The constitution at `.specify/memory/constitution.md` is the supreme authority for ALL development decisions. You MUST read it before any implementation work. Key non-negotiable rules:

- **TDD**: Red-Green-Refactor. Write failing test first, then implement, then refactor.
- **Clean Code**: No comments in production code. Functions ≤ 20 lines. Files ≤ 200 lines. Names reveal intent.
- **Atomic Commits**: Every commit = single coherent working change. Test suite passes at every commit. Conventional Commits format: `type(scope): description`. Large changes MUST be decomposed into multiple commits.
- **Design**: SOLID, DRY, KISS, YAGNI. Composition over inheritance. Dependency injection for all external deps.
- **Coverage**: ≥ 90% for statements, branches, functions, and lines.
- **Documentation**: `docs/` MUST be updated with every feature. A feature is not complete until documented. Outdated docs = bug.

## Git Operations

All git write commands (commit, push, branch, merge, rebase, tag) MUST use `required_permissions: ["all"]` to avoid sandbox blocking. This is non-negotiable — the sandbox will reject git writes without it.

## Active Technologies

- TypeScript 5.x (strict mode, no `any`)
- pnpm monorepo: packages/shared-types, packages/bot-adapters, packages/gateway, packages/cli, packages/ai-agent
- Commander.js (CLI), @inquirer/prompts (interactive prompts)
- grammY (Telegram Bot API), Discord.js (Discord Bot API)
- Vercel AI SDK (ai, @ai-sdk/openai, @ai-sdk/anthropic, @ai-sdk/google)
- Vitest (testing), oxlint (linting), Prettier (formatting), tsdown (build)

## Project Structure

```text
packages/
  shared-types/   # Core interfaces and validators
  bot-adapters/   # Telegram/Discord adapter implementations
  gateway/        # HTTP gateway server
  cli/            # CLI commands (onboard, pairing, gateway, agent)
  ai-agent/       # AI provider factory, conversation store, message processor, tools
tests/
  unit/           # Unit tests mirror packages/ structure
  integration/    # End-to-end flow tests
  contract/       # API surface contract tests
  __mocks__/      # Shared test mocks
docs/             # User-facing documentation (getting-started, CLI ref, feature guides)
specs/            # Feature specifications and plans
```

## Commands

```bash
pnpm test                # Run all tests
pnpm test:coverage       # Run tests with coverage thresholds
pnpm lint                # Run oxlint
pnpm format:check        # Check Prettier formatting
pnpm format              # Auto-fix formatting
pnpm build               # Build all packages
```

## Code Style

TypeScript 5.x strict mode. No `any`. No comments. Small functions. Dependency injection everywhere.

